An internal name to use for this campaign. By default, the campaign subject will be used.

Any entity with an empty or invalid email address field value will simply be ignored by the Mailchimp subscription system. This is why the Email field is the only required merge field which can sync to non-required fields.

Maximum number of entities to process in a single cron run. Mailchimp suggest keeping this at 5000 or below. This value is also used for batch Merge Variable updates on the Fields tab (part of mailchimp_lists).
Multi-value fields will only sync their first value to Mailchimp, as Mailchimp does not support multi-value fields.
New subscribers will be sent a link with an email they must follow to confirm their subscription.
No custom merge vars exist for the current audience.
Only 'required' and 'calculated' fields are allowed to be synced with Mailchimp 'required' merge fields.
Path to the signup page. ie "newsletter/signup".
Please check your email to confirm your subscription.
Please select at least one audience to subscribe to.

Puts all Mailchimp subscription operations into the cron queue. (Includes subscribe, update, and unsubscribe operations.) Note: May cause confusion if caches are cleared, as requested changes will appear to have failed until cron is run.
Retrieving merge fields for this audience.
Select a Mailchimp user template to use. Due to a limitation in the API, only templates that do not contain repeating sections are available. If empty, the default template will be applied.
Select an audience to sync with on the Field Settings tab before configuring the field instance.
Select an entity to import before adding the token.
Select if signup form submit should use AJAX instead of default page reload. Destination page will be ignored if checked.
Select the audience tags this campaign should be sent to.
Select the audience this campaign should be sent to.
Select the merge fields to show on registration forms. Required fields are automatically displayed.
Select which audiences to show on your signup form. You can create additional audiences at @Mailchimp.

Specify pages using their paths. The '*' character is a wildcard. Enter one path per line. %front is the front page.
If you have created a pop-up subscription form in Mailchimp, it will appear on paths defined here.
Subscribe or unsubscribe entity from a mailchimp audience
Subscription Field connected to the desired Mailchimp Audience.
Text that shows as preview in e-mail clients, but not in the mail itself.
The API key for your Mailchimp account. Get or generate a valid API key at your @apilink.
The HTML content of the campaign.
The HTML content or, if a template is selected, the content for each section.
The ID of the Mailchimp connected site linked to this site.

The label to display on the GDPR consent checkbox, for example "I agree to the privacy policy". This should coincide with what you have in Mailchimp!
The subscription service is currently unavailable. Please check again later.
The timeout (in seconds) for calls to the MailChimp API. Set to something that won't take down the Drupal site.
The title for this signup form.
There was a problem with your newsletter signup to %list.
There was a problem with your newsletter signup.
This action will delete both the Mailchimp campaign and Drupal entity and cannot be undone.
This action will send the campaign through Mailchimp and cannot be undone.
This can overwrite values configured directly on your Mailchimp Account.
This description will be shown on the signup form below the title. (500 characters or less)

This displays a list of all Mailchimp Subscription Fields
        configured on your system, with a row for each unique Instance of that field.
        To edit each field's settings, go to the Entity Bundle's configuration
        screen and use the Field UI.
        When entities with Mailchimp Subscription Fields are updated,
        the Merge Variables configured through Field UI are automatically updated if necessary.
        However, if you have existing subscribers on Mailchimp and matching Entities
        on Drupal when you configure your Merge Variables, the existing values
        are not synced automatically, as this could be a slow process.
        You can manually force updates of all existing Merge Values to existing
        Mailchimp subscribers for each field configuration using the 'Batch Update'
        option on this table. The Mailchimp Subscription Field is provided by the
        Mailchimp Audiences (mailchimp_lists) module.
This does not affect Signup Blocks; only Pages.
This group will not be visible to the end user. However you can set the default value and it will be actually used.
This is useful for "additive" form behavior, so a user adding a new interest will not have other interests removed from their Mailchimp subscription just because they failed to check the box again.

This message will appear after a successful submission of this form. Leave blank for no message, but make sure you configure a destination in that case unless you really want to confuse your site visitors.
To display Interest Groups, first enable them in the field instance settings.
True to subscribe, False to unsubscribe
